  "texts": [
    "Theorem 5.22.",
    "Let d ∈ N, d ≥ 2.",
    "For any η > 0, σ ∈ 2B L ∞ and a weak * open neighbourhood V of σ, there exists N 1∈ N such that if K ∈ N, K ≥ N 1, M ∈ N, then for any k 0 ∈ N, there exists a weak * open set U ⊂ L ∞ ([0, 1] d) having the following properties.",
    "Whenever R ∈ R ≤k 0, n ∈ {0, 1,..., K -2}, Q = Q(R, n) and Q ′ = Q(R, n + 1), then Q ρ - Q ′ ρ > r d (1 -η) for every ρ ∈ U,where r is the side length of Q and Q ′.",
    "Moreover, U contains a smooth map ρ ∈ V of norm at most 2.Proof."
  ],
